to the editor re less baseball is more op ed june 21 while rick burton 's suggestion to cut major league baseball 's teams by two to get rid of failing teams is logical it 's still too far fetched to expect players union leaders would never consider cutting the number of teams the more teams the more jobs available for players a more feasible solution to baseball 's competition problem would be to carry out a draft system in which the financially poor baseball teams could pluck away the young minor league prospects of the wealthy teams if the have not teams of baseball could monopolize these inexpensive young players they would stand a much greater chance of competing against wealthy teams like the yankees and the dodgers sam kontogiannis allendale nj june 21 2001

